text: How thought you that this thing could captivate?&& What are those graces that could make her dear,
What are those graces that could make her dear,&& Who is not worth the notice of a sneer,
Who is not worth the notice of a sneer,&& To rouse the vapid devil of her hate?
To rouse the vapid devil of her hate?&& A speech conventional, so void of weight,
A speech conventional, so void of weight,&& That after it has buzzed about one's ear,
That after it has buzzed about one's ear,&& 'Twere rich refreshment for a week to hear
'Twere rich refreshment for a week to hear%% The dentist babble or the barber prate;
The dentist babble or the barber prate;&& A hand displayed with many a little art;
A hand displayed with many a little art;&& An eye that glances on her neighbor's dress;
An eye that glances on her neighbor's dress;&& A foot too often shown for my regard;
A foot too often shown for my regard;&& An angel's form -- a waiting-woman's heart;
An angel's form -- a waiting-woman's heart;&& A perfect-featured face, expressionless,
A perfect-featured face, expressionless,&& Insipid, as the Queen upon a card.
